data.description: Genetic basis of morphological, physiological and behavioral variations within and between human populations, and their origins and evolution.
data.title: PRINCIPLES OF BIOLOGICAL ANTHROPOLOGY

data.description: The evolution of the Hominoidea is reconstructed from direct and indirect evidence. Cladistic and phylogenetic analyses are used to study the relationships among species. Interpretations of the fossil record are presented from a historical perspective, focusing on the hominoid-hominid transition.
data.title: HOMINOID EVOLUTION
